.TH "batadv_hardif_neigh_get" 9 "batadv_hardif_neigh_get" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
batadv_hardif_neigh_get \- retrieve a hardif neighbour from the list
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "struct batadv_hardif_neigh_node *" batadv_hardif_neigh_get
.BI "(const struct batadv_hard_iface *hard_iface "  ","
.BI "const u8 *neigh_addr "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "hard_iface" 12
the interface where this neighbour is connected to
.IP "neigh_addr" 12
the address of the neighbour
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Looks for and possibly returns a neighbour belonging to this hard interface.
.SH "RETURN"
neighbor when found. Otherwise NULL
